This paper deals with the problem of learning classifiers from noisy labels, which is a common problem in machine learning. The proposed method uses a regularized correntropy framework to learn the classifiers, which is a technique that has been widely used in the fields of signal processing and control theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel learning algorithm that involves optimizing an objective function, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
